HEADWORD: Crowberry
<hw>Crow`ber`ry</hw> <pr>(kr?"b?r`r?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A heathlike plant of the genus
<gen>Empetrum</gen>, and its fruit, a black, scarcely edible berry; --
also called <altname>crakeberry</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

